title: build: Bump dependencies
fix(debuginfo): Decompress GNU compressed debug sections correctly
body: This fixes decompression of `.zdebug*` GNU sections.

title: feat(common): Support name serialization and deserialization
body: We need to send these across procspawn.

title: test(python): test against python3.6
body:
I'm targetting Python 3.6 support for sentry, so this makes linux-python test against python3.6 instead of the default 3.5. If 3.5 support is desired I can just add another matrix job.

Note that mac-python appears to be 3.7.5, so it should just work.

title: fix: Using Hermes SourceMaps with non-hermes stackframes
body: This was a misunderstanding on my part. The `SourceMapHermes` actually is not specific to Hermes at all. It’s just a SourceMap with additional scoping information. So it can be used without Hermes.

title: feat(minidump): Implement serde traits for ProcessResult
feat: Support react-native hermes sourcemaps
body: This treats Hermes SourceMaps slightly differently, resolving the scope name via the bytecode offset.

title: build: Bump minimum macOS version to 10.13
fix(cabi): Consistently free strings obtained from the C-ABI
body: We did not consistently call `free=True` on strings returned from the C-ABI. This PR updates docs and adds the flags where appropriate.

title: fix(unreal): Remove the first line from the Unreal Log
body: The first line is a header and should not end up as a log entry.

title: fix(unreal): Fix typo in ContextRuntimeProperties
feat(unreal): Expose context and logs parsing
body: We need to expose context and logs parsing in order to be able to store them separately (in some envelope) and then, at a latter time, parse them independently.

title: fix(debuginfo): Improve `.o` handling on MachO (#173)
body:
I am using `symbolic_debuginfo` in a [symbolicator](https://github.com/mozilla/fix-stacks) used for stack traces produced by Firefox.

On Mac, we don't build dSYMs by default because doing so is slow. So I want to emulate `atos`, which is able to read debuginfo from a binary by consulting the binary's symbol table and then reading debug info from the object files and archive files mentioned.
         
I have this working, but it requires a couple of small changes to `symbolic_debuginfo`, due to slight differences between `.o` files and executables/libraries.

title: fix: Harden macho multi arch parsing code.
body:
This fixes a mis detection of class files as macho fat files by using a
heuristic to tell the files apart based on on number of macho embedded
architectures vs class file versions.

Additionally it changes the slicing code to manual slicing which prevents
us panicking if we accidentally read bad ranges from a macho file.  This
happend commonly when we mis-characterized class files as macho fat files.
